soc.message

Class SOCResetBoardVote

  • java.lang.Object
    • soc.message.SOCMessage
      • soc.message.SOCMessageForGame
        • soc.message.SOCMessageTemplate2i
          • soc.message.SOCResetBoardVote
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class SOCResetBoardVote
extends SOCMessageTemplate2i
    This bi-directional message gives the client's vote on a "board reset", which was requested by another player in that game.
    • This message to server is in response to a SOCResetBoardRequest sent earlier this turn to all non-robot clients. (Robots' vote is always Yes.)
    • Followed by (from server, to all game member clients) SOCResetBoardVote with that player number, informing all players of the client's vote.
    • Once voting is complete, server sends to all either a SOCResetBoardAuth or SOCResetBoardReject message.
    For details of messages sent, see SOCServer.resetBoardAndNotify(String, int).
    Since:
    1.1.00
    Author:
    Jeremy D Monin <jeremy@nand.net>
